[Patient] What foods can I eat to help manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, and lean proteins for a healthy heart.
[Patient] Are there affordable options since I'm on a tight budget?
[Educator] Look for discounts at local food banks, farmers markets, and community gardens.
[Patient] It's hard to get fresh produce in my neighborhood. Any suggestions?
[Educator] Consider transportation services or delivery options for groceries. Community resources may help.
[Patient] Can you recommend some budget-friendly meal planning strategies?
[Educator] Plan meals ahead, buy in bulk, and use leftovers creatively to save money.